        <footer class="report-footer">
            <p>
                <strong>EU AI Act Risk Classification Report</strong>
                <br>
                {{ organization_name | default_value('Organization') }} | Generated: {{ generated_at | format_datetime }}
                <br>
                Document Version: {{ document_version | default_value('1.0') }} | Generator Version: {{ generator_version | default_value('1.0.0') }}
            </p>
            <div class="legal-notice">
                <strong>Legal Notice:</strong> This document has been generated to support EU AI Act compliance requirements.
                Risk classifications should be reviewed by qualified personnel and legal advisors to ensure accuracy.
                The EU AI Act (Regulation (EU) 2024/1689) entered into force on 1 August 2024, with provisions
                applying at different dates. Organizations must ensure compliance by the applicable deadlines.
                This document is intended for internal compliance purposes and should be kept up to date as
                AI systems and regulatory guidance evolve.
                <br><br>
                ACGS-2 Enterprise Guardrails Platform - Compliance Documentation Service
            </div>
        </footer>
    </div>
</body>
